The comfortable rate for an investment loan is 10-13%.
According to experts, the small and medium-sized business lending market in January-April of this year declined by 40%.
What do you think the situation is today?
After the panic moods of the end of 2014 - the beginning of 2015, the volume of loans of SMEs decreased significantly.
The reason is clear: a sharp increase in interest rates.
Loans below 25-30% per annum were not beneficial to anyone.
If previously the bank could put at an increased rate all its possible problems in the future, from delays to non-returns, then now it is impossible to do this: rates and so cloudy.
For businesses, the current level of rates on MSB loans is uncomfortable.
For a significant part of investment projects, the current level is unacceptable in terms of their affordability.
The 10-13% rate would allow businesses to invest in a wide range of projects and form attractive returns on them.
How satisfied do you think the demand for loans from entrepreneurs is?
After the decline of the Central Bank interest rate, the situation improved slightly.
Credit resources have become more accessible.
However, according to our observations, customers began to apply for loans much less often.
First of all, the business does not understand the prospects of its development and future revenues.
Today, business has one way out: it is necessary to learn to work, focusing on the current economic situation in the country and the region.
It is necessary to monitor the current results more closely, to control the movement of money.
At the same time, with the availability of financial resources, it is worth using new technologies to modernize the equipment, reduce the cost of production and energy supply.
