What are the main trends in the ICB lending market that will strengthen and affect its development by the end of 2015?
Will the interest rate change?
The forecast for the reduction of the average rate will depend largely on the policy of the Central Bank, and now the regulator is demonstrating consistency in the issue of the reduction of the key rate.
However, the radical fall in the price of loans for SMEs is not worth waiting for.
In the current situation, the problem, first of all, is inflation, which makes the necessary higher interest rate to generate real income.
In addition, the cost of money in Russia will remain high even if the central bank rates are lowered.
If we talk about the level of latency, then traditionally small and medium-sized companies, limited in both the possibilities of replenishment of funds and in the options of correction of economic behavior, will certainly pose a greater risk to creditors.
I would not expect a significant reduction in the share of bad loans.
