The White House confirms Xi Jinping's visit to Washington
The White House on Tuesday confirmed in an official statement that Chinese President Xi Jinping will arrive with an official visit to the United States at the end of this month.
This visit — Xi Jinping’s first visit to Washington — will take place on September 25 and will be a response visit to President Barack Obama’s visit to Beijing in November last year, the statement said.
U.S. President and First Lady Michelle Obama will also host Xi Jinping and his wife Pen Liyuan at a government dinner on the evening of the same day after the two leaders hold bilateral talks.
“President Xi Jinping’s visit will provide an opportunity to expand cooperation between the U.S. and China on common, regional and bilateral issues of interest to both sides, and will also allow U.S. and Chinese presidents to approach the issues in question constructively,” the statement said.
